  "prompt": "Is the test taker report for GMAT accessible immediately after the test ? It\u2019s not the official score report that GMAC sends after 15-20 days.",
  "response": "The **test taker report** for the GMAT is **not available immediately** after the test. However, you do receive an **unofficial score report** right after completing the exam, which includes your **Quantitative, Verbal, Integrated Reasoning, and Total scores**. This unofficial report excludes the **Analytical Writing Assessment (AWA)** score, as that section is evaluated separately and takes additional time.\n\nThe **official score report** from GMAC (Graduate Management Admission Council) is typically sent within **7 to 20 days** after the test and includes your AWA score. This is the report that is sent to the schools you selected during the test registration process.\n\nSo, to clarify:\n\n1. **Unofficial Score Report**: Available immediately after the test (excluding AWA).\n2. **Official Score Report**: Sent by GMAC within 7 to 20 days (includes AWA).\n\nIf you're referring to something other than these two, please clarify, as there isn\u2019t a separate \"test taker report\" provided immediately.",
